definition: to monopolize/to seize/to take into one's arms/to embrace/to fasten (with a rope etc)/to take on (responsibility etc)/to canvass

sentences.english: Take time to dream; it will take you to the stars.
sentences.chinese: 花點時間夢想，它給你九天攬月之志。

sentences.english: In youth, we clothe ourselves with rainbows, and go as brave as the zodiac.
sentences.chinese: 青春年華，能把彩虹作衣，敢上九天攬月。
